def verify_values():
    # Valores Unicos
    for name_col in X.columns.tolist():
        print('-'*100)
        print('Column: ', name_col)
        print(X[name_col].unique())
        print(X[name_col].value_counts())
        print('nan_value:', X[name_col].isnull().sum())

from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer, KNNImputer

# verify_values()
fields_imputer = {'edad': 'mean', 'sueldo_smdlv': 'mean', 'otros_ingresos_smdlv': 'mean', 'genero': 'most_frequent',
                  'estado_civil': 'most_frequent', 'municipio_expedicion': 'most_frequent', 'sector': 'most_frequent',
                  'municipio_nacimiento': 'most_frequent', 'tiene_casa_propia': 'most_frequent'}

for key in fields_imputer:
    print('-'*50)
    print('Column:', key)
    imputer = SimpleImputer(missing_values=np.NaN, strategy=fields_imputer[key])
    print('\t{} with nan: {}'.format(key, X[key].isna().sum()))
    X[key] = imputer.fit_transform(X[key].values.reshape(-1,1), y.values.reshape(-1,1))[:,0]
    print('\t{} with out nan: {}'.format(key, X[key].isna().sum()))
    print('\t', X[key].values[:5])

from sklearn.preprocessing import OrdinalEncoder, LabelEncoder, OneHotEncoder
ord_enc = OrdinalEncoder()
one_enc = OneHotEncoder()
for name_col in obj_df.columns.tolist():
    print('-'*100)
    num_class = len(X[name_col].unique())
    print('Column: ', name_col, ' Num Class:', num_class)
    if num_class == 2:
        X[name_col+'_code'] = ord_enc.fit_transform(X[[name_col]])
    else:
        X[name_col+'_code'] = ord_enc.fit_transform(X[[name_col]])

from imblearn import FunctionSampler  # to use a idendity sampler
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE, ADASYN, RandomOverSampler
from collections import Counter

X_vm = X.select_dtypes(exclude=['object']).copy()
print(Counter(y))
# define oversampling strategy
oversample = SMOTE()
# fit and apply the transform
X_over, y_over = oversample.fit_resample(X_vm, y)
# summarize class distribution
print(Counter(y_over))

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_over, y_over , test_size = 0.30, random_state = 101)#Creating the prediction model
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
log_model = LogisticRegression(max_iter = 1000)
log_model.fit(X_train, y_train)#Performance Check
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix, roc_curve,auc, accuracy_score
predictions = log_model.predict(X_test)
print(accuracy_score(y_test, predictions))
print(classification_report(y_test,predictions))

#Creating the ROC-AUC plot
preds = log_model.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]

plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))
plt.title('Receiver Operator Characteristic')
